3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 41-11-7 be AMENDED:
5 41-11-7. Except as permitted by statute, no person otherwise provided in this
6 section, an individual may not take or, have in possession, or intentionally break or destroy
7 any nest or the eggs of the kinds of birds, the taking or killing of which is at any time or
8 at all times prohibited. A violation of this section is a Class 2 misdemeanor.
9 Nothing in this section prohibits any egg salvage activity if:
10 (1) The individual holds a migratory bird special purpose salvage permit, issued by the
11 United States Fish and Wildlife Service, in accordance with 50 C.F.R § 21.95
12 (January 1, 2026); and
13 (2) The salvage activity does not involve the eggs of birds, the taking or killing of which
14 is at all times prohibited.
